        <td bgcolor="dimgray" colspan="2" valign="top">
		<img src="icon_posticon.gif" border="0" hspace="3"><font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="1">Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;03/16/2002&nbsp;:&nbsp; 15:07:35</font>

		&nbsp;<a href="pop_profile.asp?mode=display&id=638"><img src="icon_profile.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Show Profile" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>
 
			&nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('pop_mail.asp?id=638')"><img src="icon_email.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Email Poster" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=TopicQuote&TOPIC_ID=1554&FORUM_ID=6&CAT_ID=1&Forum_Title=The+Great+Necro+Talks+2002&Topic_Title=Essence+emeralds+need+an+overhaul"><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"> I've played EQ as a necro for over 2 years now and in that time I have largely ignored the so-called necro "rez" as being too costly to cast and too prohibitive. To have to sacrifice a high level player is essential stealing exp from one player and giving it back to another player. A cleric can rez for just the cost of mana and many have the epic.</P><P>We just saw that Verant will be giving lower level clerics more rez options which is an attempt to make this game more user friendly. I think we need to see the same kind of effort with regard to the Necro rez and Essence Emeralds. Here are some suggestions:</P><P>-remove the lvl 60 cap on casting Sacrifice (with the advent of AA exp, exp is now being used and sought after by lvl 60 players)</P><P>-introduce a new spell called Sacrifice I lvl 29 which creates an Essence Ruby enables you to sacrifice a lvl 29 and up player for a 50% exp rez (clerics get revive at lvl 29 and now have many more rez spells this is only fair)</P><P>-change the name of Sacrifice to Sacrifice II and allow it to be cast on lvl 40+ players to produce an Essence Emerald (this would really help get more EE's into circulation)</P><P>-start including Essence Emeralds as loot on high level mobs equivalent to the drop rate of Blue Diamonds (this would create a market for the EE's and help necros actually start using this spell)</P><P>-create special tailoring, smithing and jewelery recipes that require Essence Emeralds that bestow special powers to the resulting tradeskill item</P><P>Honestly, Verant needs to make some kind of effort to put more Essence Emeralds into circulation. Clerics who are a class that are very popular just got a massive power boost in their rez abilites yet necros who are on the fringes of viabililty got nothing to augment our so-called "rez". Please Verant look into this.</P><P><BR>Dornette<BR>60 necromancer (retired)<BR>The Nameless</font></td>

      </tr>

